  symmetric/Hermitian tridiagonal matrices

    Examples
    --------
    >>> import numpy as np
    >>> from scipy import linalg
    >>> a = np.array([[0., -1.], [1., 0.]])
    >>> linalg.eigvals(a)
    array([0.+1.j, 0.-1.j])

    >>> b = np.array([[0., 1.], [1., 1.]])
    >>> linalg.eigvals(a, b)
    array([ 1.+0.j, -1.+0.j])

    >>> a = np.array([[3., 0., 0.], [0., 8., 0.], [0., 0., 7.]])
   